  "text": "In Equation [CITATION_1] , g(z) is a clipped rectified linear unit (ReLu) activation function that is used to calculate the output at hidden layers, W (l) represents the weight matrix, and b (l) is the bias vector at layer l. In order to avoid the vanishing gradient problem, ReLu functions are chosen over sigmoid functions.",
